item.title: @AlishaMarie talks Vlogmas, DIY fails, and her most viral video | YouTube Watch History
item.description: Did someone say vlogmas?!?! The Holidays are upon us and YouTube’s OG vlogmas creator, Alisha Marie, sits down to share what’s in her YouTube Watch History. As she gears up for her 10th year of vlogmas, we get a peak at what festive content she’s been watching to prepare. From dishing on her biggest DIY fails, to her viral catfish moment, to her favorite vloggers of all time, Alisha Marie tells all on what she’s been watching and what she’d recommend this holiday season! 0:00 - 0:20 Intro 0:20 - 3:13 Recent Videos 3:13 - 5:21 Keyword Search 5:21 - 9:06 Scavenger Hunt 9:06 - 11:07 Holiday Spirit Playlist 11:07 Final Thoughts #AlishaMarie #YouTube #WatchHistory #Vlogmas

item.title: How @NymaTang helped change the beauty industry | #YouTubeBlack presents Flowers
item.description: Nyma Tang gets the flowers she deserves, here and now, for her series The Darkest Shade, which sparked a conversation on YouTube around the need for inclusion in the beauty industry. Online video trends have evolved to become the driving force of pop culture. But do you know who’s creating them? From the moment of upload, discover the untold, true stories of the Black creators and culture behind your favorite trends. Watch sWooZie’s story here: http://yt.be/SwoozieFlowers Bianca Bonnie’s story coming Jan 18th.
